tails":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Ministry of Housing,<br/>Communities &amp;<br/>Local Government","crest":"single-identity"},"brand":"department-for-communities-and-local-government","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/124/s300_2_Marsham_Street_960x640.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/124/s960_2_Marsham_Street_960x640.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/ministry-of-housing-communities-and-local-government","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ministry-of-housing-communities-and-local-government"}],"roles":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state--91","base_path":"/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state--91","content_id":"8b9f67df-4acd-4c91-b48e-3635952fb4a7","document_type":"ministerial_role","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2018-01-15T15:36:31Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Parliamentary Under Secretary of State (Minister for Local Government)","withdrawn":false,"details":{"body":"<p>The minister is responsible for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Local government policy, including local government reform</li>\n  <li>Local government finances (including local authority sustainability and business rates retention)</li>\n  <li>Adult social care</li>\n  <li>Local government interventions policy and oversight of existing interventions</li>\n  <li>Local government pensions</li>\n  <li>Troubled Families</li>\n  <li>Parks / green space</li>\n</ul>\n"},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state--91","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state--91"},{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-housing-communities-and-local-government","base_path":"/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-housing-communities-and-local-government","content_id":"10a5db51-4c19-44c4-93d4-a09acc423220","document_type":"ministerial_role","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2018-04-30T10:49:45Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government","withdrawn":false,"details":{"body":"<p>The minister is responsible for the overall leadership and strategic direction of the department.</p>\n"},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-housing-communities-and-local-government","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-housing-communities-and-local-government"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Brexit Local Government Delivery Board: March 2019 update","public_updated_at":"2019-04-01T12:25:54Z","document_type":"press_release","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/brexit-local-government-delivery-board-march-2019-update","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/brexit-local-government-delivery-board-march-2019-update","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"5f89a028-d4b9-469c-820d-32b9a277f8f0","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/brexit-local-government-delivery-board-march-2019-update","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/brexit-local-government-delivery-board-march-2019-update","links":{}}]},"description":"Update from meetings held on 26 February and 18 March.","details":{"body":"<p>The Government Brexit Delivery Board has been meeting more frequently as the UK prepares to leave the EU, with recent meetings taking place on both 26 February and 18 March.</p>\n\n<p>Communities Secretary, Rt Hon James Brokenshire MP, chaired the February meeting at which representatives from the Local Government Association, County Councils Network, District Councils Network and London Councils, provided updates and feedback.</p>\n\n<p>Government ministers from <abbr title=\"Department for Exiting the European Union\">DExEU</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Department of Health and Social Care\">DHSC</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Department for Education\">DfE</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Department for Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs\">DEFRA</abbr> and a senior official from <abbr title=\"Department for Transport\">DfT</abbr> were in attendance to discuss departmental preparations.</p>\n\n<p>Local Government Minister, Rishi Sunak MP, chaired the March meeting.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to the broad range of English local government representation, representatives of devolved administration councils - Convention of Scottish Local Authorities (COSLA), Northern Ireland Local Government Association (NILGA) and Welsh Local Government Association (WLGA) - were in attendance â€“ having been invited by the Communities Secretary to hear an update from Home Office Minister, Rt Hon Caroline Nokes MP.</p>\n\n<p>The minister provided a comprehensive update on the UK Settled Status Scheme ahead of its launch on 30 March.</p>\n\n<div id=\"contact_bfc00333-a9ee-4ca1-9d3c-432dbcdf4640\" class=\"contact postal-address\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Office address and general enquiries</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n      <p class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"street-address\">2 Marsham Street\n<br>\nLondon</span><br>\n<span class=\"postal-code\">SW1P 4DF</span>\n</p>\n\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n      \n        <p class=\"contact_form_url\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Contact form</span>\n          <a href=\"https://forms.communities.gov.uk/\">https://forms.communit...</a>\n        </p>\n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">General enquiries:  please use this number if you are a member of the public</span>\n          030 3444 0000\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"contact_c1f13fd8-9feb-4028-9323-7cb3383323b4\" class=\"contact\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Media enquiries</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n        <p class=\"email\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Email</span>\n          <a href=\"mailto:newsdesk@communities.gov.uk\" class=\"email\">newsdesk@communities.gov.uk</a>\n        </p>\n      \n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Please use this number if you are a journalist wishing to speak to Press Office</span>\n          0303 444 1209\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"contact_f375ee5c-c7f3-4e09-9ba8-2ca0308481c5\" class=\"contact\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Social media - MHCLG</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n    \n    \n      <p class=\"comments\">Twitter - <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mhclg\">https://twitter.com/mhclg</a><br>Flickr - <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/mhclg\">http://www.flickr.com/photos/mhclg</a><br>LinkedIn - <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/company/mhclg\">http://www.linkedin.com/company/mhclg</a></p>\n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-04-01T12:24:46.874Z"}]},"document_status":"published_but_needs_2i","created_by":"John Long","last_updated_by":"Sophia Danenberg","political":true,"government":{"title":"2015 Conservative government","slug":"2015-conservative-government","start_date":"2015-05-07T23:00:00.000Z","end_date":"","current":true},"document_schema":"news"}